title: United States - annual real GDP 1990 to 2019
yAxis: GDP in billion chained (2012) U.S. dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes GDP in billion chained (2012) U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 30.
In general GDP in billion chained (2012) U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 1998 and 1999.
Maximum GDP in billion chained (2012) U.S. dollars, about 19072.5 was reported at Year 2019
The lowest GDP in billion chained (2012) U.S. dollars, of value 9355.4 was reported at Year 1991
